Iavan Pijoos, News24Durban &ndash; He lay quietly wrapped in a black T-shirt under a tree in Palmiet Road, Clare Hills, in Durban.His placenta was still attached when a woman walking past found him.Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said the newborn was found on Saturday afternoon at around 14:30.Botha said paramedics applied cord clamps and then cut the umbilical cord to free the baby.He said it was still unclear who abandoned the baby.His condition was stabilised and he was cleaned before being transported to a nearby hospital.Police are investigating. A newborn baby found under a tree in Durban on Saturday afternoon. (Supplied)24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.